VRChat 위키에 오신 것을 환영합니다. 저희 지식 기반 구축에 관심을 가져주셔서 기쁩니다

여기서는 다음과 같은 내용을 다룹니다:

* VRChat은 어떻게 사용하나요?

* VRChat 조작법은 무엇인가요?

* VRChat에서 X를 하려면 어떻게 해야 하나요?

* VRChat에서 월드나 아바타를 만들려면 어떻게 시작해야 하나요?

VRChat에는 월드와 아바타만 있는 게 아니에요! 커뮤니티 허브([[Special:MyLanguage/VRCWiki:Community Hub|커뮤니티 허브]])에서도 커뮤니티 활동에 참여하실 수 있습니다! 다양한 가이드와 정보를 찾아보실 수 있어요. 허브에 방문하셔서 탐색해 보세요! 크리에이터이거나 VRChat의 크리에이터 컴패니언 또는 SDK 사용에 관심이 있으시다면, 크리에이터 문서({{VRC link|https://creators.vrchat.com/|Creator Documentation}})도 참고해 보세요. VRChat에서 콘텐츠를 제작하는 데 필요한 기술적인 문서가 담겨 있습니다.

== 위키에 기여하기 ==
VRChat 계정으로 로그인하면 계정 상태가 양호한 한 이 위키에 기여할 수 있습니다! 먼저 [[Special:MyLanguage/VRCWiki:Guidelines|지침]]을 읽고 [[Special:MyLanguage/VRCWiki:Neutral_point_of_view|중립적인 관점]]으로 글을 쓰는 것이 무엇을 의미하는지 이해해 주세요. <u>본인 콘텐츠</u>에 대한 문서를 작성하거나 편집하거나, 회사 또는 조직을 대신하여 문서를 작성하거나 편집하려는 경우, 게시하기 전에 VRCWiki의 [[Special:MyLanguage/VRCWiki:Conflicts of interest|이해 충돌 정책]]을 읽어봐야 합니다.

== 네임스페이스 ==
VRChat 위키에는 편집자가 숙지해야 할 네임스페이스가 있습니다. 이러한 네임스페이스를 사용하면 문서를 작성하고 검색할 때 유용합니다.

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''VRChat''' - <code>No Prefix</code> - Official VRChat Wiki pages. Changes to VRChat articles made by you, and other editors will require moderation approval, and will appear after being reviewed. These articles primarily feature content created by VRChat itself, or be generalized topics. This also covers official applications and software, such as the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat Creator Companion|VRChat Creator Companion]], and the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat SDK|VRChat SDK]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''Community''' - Prefix: <code>Community:</code> - The community namespace. Pages here should be focused on community pages, hubs, and creations. This also covers community applications and software, such as Unity, Blender, and prefabs. Everyone can edit these pages directly. [[Special:MyLanguage/:Category:Worlds|World pages]], [[Special:MyLanguage/:Category:Avatars|Avatar pages]], [[Special:MyLanguage/:Category:Guides|Guides]] and [[Special:MyLanguage/:Category:Resources|Resources]] belong here.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''Guides''' - Prefix: <code>Guides:</code> - Articles in the guides namespace focus on how to accomplish a task, troubleshoot a problem, or describe advanced topics in complexity. Guides should remain proactive, and relevant to VRChat, Unity, and other similar software.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''Category''' - Prefix: <code>Category:</code> - These namespaces are for classifications and arranging ambiguations into organized lists, such as <nowiki>''Category:Community Content''</nowiki>
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''VRCWiki''' - Prefix: <code>VRCWiki:</code> - Namespace for pages in relation to the VRChat Wiki.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''User''' - Prefix: <code>User:</code> - The user namespace is the "home page" of an editor. You can edit your own user page, as long as it follows VRChat's guidelines. Adding to another editor's talk page is the equivalent of publicly messaging them.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''Special''' - Prefix: <code>Special:</code> - Namespace for special pages.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Creating a new page ==
To create a new page, ensure you are logged in and [https://wiki.vrchat.com/index.php?search= search] for what you would like to have as a title of that page. Should a page with that title not exist yet, an option appears to create it.<blockquote>Create the page "<span style="color:red">Your Search Query</span>" on this wiki!</blockquote>
Clicking this red link will direct you to creating a new page.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Please note that to create pages in the Community namespace requires to have <code>Community:</code> as a prefix of the page title. For Example: <code>Community:World Name</code>. Read more about when to use which namespace [[Special:MyLanguage/VRCWiki:How_to_Contribute#Namespaces|above]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Uploading images ==
When uploading images to the VRChat Wiki, you can go to the [[Special:Upload|Upload file]] page to do so. These images can be then embedded to any article that you edit. Please be sure to give a brief description or caption of the image in "Summary", but more importantly, please select the proper Licensing! While the supported file types include "png, gif, jpg, jpeg," and "webp", it is commonly best practice to upload still images using the .webp format, since it retains quality while being very optimized, compared to the .png format which takes lots of space. Keep in mind that the maximum file size to upload to the Wiki is only 20 megabytes per image, so please try converting your pictures to .webp format.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Do not write articles about yourself or other users ==
VRChat Wiki is a knowledgebase to write about VRChat content such as features, prefabs, and worlds. This Wiki is not a place to post personal information about yourself, or other users. Feel free to create and add onto your personal User: page, or interact with another editor using the Talk/Discussion page on another User: page.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==VRChat has Content Gating==
VRChat is a platform for users 13 and over, per the {{VRC link|https://hello.vrchat.com/legal | Terms of Service}}. So is this Wiki! Please refrain from referencing explicit adult or violent content. Be considerate on what you are writing about.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Discussion Page==
[[File:DiscussionPageHighlighted.webp|thumb|A link to the Discussion Tab is present on the top left of every page.]]
Each page also has a discussion page, which is used to talk about contents of a page.
Please make a new header for each subject with a title and with what you would like to discuss.
When you finish writing a post, add <code><nowiki>~~~~</nowiki></code> right after it . This will automatically add your username and timestamp at the end of a paragraph.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Example:<br>
<code>==New Discussion Topic==</code><br>
<code>Text discussing  something. --Another User (talk) 00:00, 22 June 2024 (UTC)</code><br>
<code>: your reply to the Discussion Topic. <nowiki>~~~~</nowiki></code>
</div>